                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d606">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">793.94/5462: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in China (<persName corresp="frus1932v03#p_JNT1"
                            type="from">Johnson</persName>) to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Peiping</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1932-08-01T18:00:00+08:00"
                            >August 1, 1932—6 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received August 1—6:03 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>882. Your 230, July 29, 6 p.m.<note n="98" xml:id="d606fn98">See footnote 13,
                            <ref target="#pg_186">p. 186</ref>.</note> Question, if it should arise,
                    will be very difficult for us to handle. I anticipate that the diplomatic body
                    may act as a whole to endeavor to persuade Japanese to retire or to be interned.
                    Japanese attitude in the past, however, has been that they are acting to protect
                    lives and property and I anticipate that they will refuse to retire or be
                    interned. Should the question arise I shall here urge my colleagues to recommend
                    joint action at Tokyo and we will do what we can to persuade the Japanese to
                    leave protection of their people and their Legation to us.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="frus1932v03#p_JNT1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Johnson</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
